description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "Near the viaduct over the railroad tracks in the heart of the city of Copenhagen there stands a monument which is distinctive of the nation's attitude toward agriculture. It has been referred to as the Danish farmer's statue of Liberty. It commemorates their relief from laws of serfdom."
